For Miss Todd thereupon handed Frank and Joe an order for a handsome motion picture camera, something they had long wished to own. To Chet and Biff she gave each a gold watch and chain.\par
''Speech! Speech!'' shouted the other boys, as the recipients of the gifts stammered their thanks.\par
After considerable pressure, Frank was at last prevailed upon to say a few words.\par
"I'm not a very good orator," he said.\par
210 The Secret of the Caves\par
"You're a better detective," shouted one of the lads at the table.\par
Perhaps he was-and Joe, too. One can decide in "The Mystery of Cabin Island."\par
"I'm not a very good orator," Frank said, "but I certainly want to thank Miss Todd very much indeed, although we don't deserve such a beautiful present."\par
